<div class="text-block row">
	<div class="large-8 columns large-offset-2">
		<h4>General Filter Logic</h4>
		<p>I laid out high-level logic for how all the filters would work together, such as:
			<ul>
				<li><span>We would only display and enable filters that would reflect available inventory. That is, the user should not be able to click on an option that would return null results.</span></li>
				<li><span>If a facet only returned one filter option, we wouldn't show the facet at all.</span></li>
				<li><span>The first option for every facet would be subtractive (AND); multiple options selected within a facet would be additive (OR).</span></li>
				<li><span>Facets would be collapsible. We could utilize data post-launch to help inform if any facets should be collapsed by default.</span></li>
				<li><span>For the MVP, I recommended non-sticky filters (e.g., the filters would not stick to the top). It was a potentially nice-to-have, as the user could easily access filters no matter how deep in the page they were, but because modifying filters would refresh the page and bring them to the top of the results anyway, I didn't see it as an extra or known benefit.</dynali>
			</ul>
		</p>
		<img src="img/work/okl-directed/sketches.jpg">
		<p class="caption">Initial exploratory sketches.</p>

	</div>
</div>

